<sections><clause id="_ac2de8f0-87cf-4493-972e-d0f0b82492e7" unnumbered="true" obligation="normative">

<p id="_236decf0-d82a-4bfc-9716-c18a7c7f626c">
<strong><sup>27</sup>Al<sup>+</sup> ion, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="normal"><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mtext>&#160;</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msub><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>s</mi><mn>3</mn><mi>p</mi><msup><mrow><mtext>&#160;</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></stem> unperturbed optical transition</strong>
</p>
</clause>
<clause id="_recommended_value_of_the_frequency" obligation="normative"><title>Recommended value <eref type="inline" bibitemid="ci2013" citeas="[1]"/> of the frequency</title><p id="_6b5e4622-9fe7-4bbd-9f51-f68d2ea46e7c">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>f</mi><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext/></mrow><mrow><mn>27</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="normal"><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>+</mtext></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1121015393207857.3</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu31"><mi mathvariant="normal">Hz</mi></mrow>









</math></stem>
</p>
<p id="_10a2159c-0790-4166-a419-f5b20bfca747">equivalent to</p>
<p id="_ecaa0faa-eee7-4686-a976-5ff91b7cfaef"><stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>&#955;</mi></mstyle><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext/></mrow><mrow><mn>27</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="normal"><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>267429385.730489</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_fm"><mi mathvariant="normal">fm</mi></mrow>








</math></stem>,</p>
<p id="_a2d669ae-30ab-49e8-bf1b-86a68e68ce97">with an estimated relative standard uncertainty of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>1.9</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></mrow></msup></math></stem>.</p>
<p id="_5c5111e6-dd89-49b8-a05f-b6574db72f07">This radiation was endorsed as a secondary representation of the
definition of the second.</p></clause>
